commit_message:
Create a description file for each image

Create a directory, and put image into the directory with
a description file.

The description file is under json format, looks like:

{
    "basic": {
        "os": "ubuntu",
        "sahara-image-elements": "2015.2.0.dev50",
        "dib-utils": "0.0.8",
        "diskimage-builder": "0.1.46"
    },
    "image": {
        "name" : "ubuntu_sahara_vanilla_hadoop_1_latest",
        "disk_format": "qcow2",
        "container_format": "bare",
        "username": "ubuntu"
    },
    "plugin": {
        "name": "vanilla"
    },
    "element": {
        "mysql": null,
        "openjdk": null,
        "hadoop": {
            "version": "1.2.1"
        },
        "process": {
            "zookeeper":null,
            "hive":null,
            "oozie":null
        },
        "libs": {
            "extjs": null,
            "swift_hadoop": null
        }
    }
}

Partial-Implements: bp expose-elements

